Package Utils

Class StreamList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • Utils.StreamList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the list elements.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable

    public class StreamList<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Iterable
    This class implements a bidirectionally linked list, where the elements may be concrete items or streams. The main purpose of this class is to implement streams which traverse a tree or graph depth-first or breadth-first.

      class  StreamList.SLIterator

      • stream

        public static <T> java.util.stream.Stream<T> stream​(T start,
                                                    boolean back,
                                                    java.util.function.Function<T,java.util.stream.Stream<T>> function)
        generates a stream where the elements are provided by a function that produces a stream. This method can be used to traverse trees or dags in breadth-first or depth-first way. In this case the function must generate the next layer of nodes in the tree or dag.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the elements
        Parameters:
        start - a start node
        back - if true then the new elements are treated later (breadth-first), otherwise they are treated first (depth-first).
        function - the function that generates for each element a new stream.
        Returns:
        a stream of the elements which ar generated by the function.
